sql:
SELECT name, brand, address, established_date
FROM businesses
ORDER BY established_date DESC;

SELECT COUNT(business_id) AS number_of_businesses
FROM businesses
WHERE suburb = 'Suburb Name';

SELECT suburb, COUNT(*) AS business_count
FROM businesses
GROUP BY suburb;

SELECT name 
FROM businesses 
ORDER BY established_date DESC;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT business_id)
FROM reviews
WHERE rating > 4.0;

external_knowledge:
- "vast ocean of public opinion" refers to the pool of reviews available for businesses; 
- "waves (reviews)" symbolizes individual reviews left by customers; 
- "weathered" means how many reviews a business has received.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(business_id) AS total_businesses
FROM businesses
WHERE suburb = 'Huonville';

external_knowledge:
- 'identity' refers to the unique identifier for each business;
- 'names' are the names of the businesses;
- 'highest buzz' refers to businesses with the most reviews;
- 'reviews' are the feedback entries associated with each business.

